1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
This year I decided to really get into the spirit of Halloween.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Ah!

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Ah!

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Ah!

5
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
It may have been the costliest decision I've ever made.

7
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
My greased up head went into the pumpkin no problem, but...

8
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,000
It won't budge.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,000
I can't get it out.

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Try again.

11
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
I mean, I could try destroying the pumpkin.

12
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,000
No, no, no, no!

13
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
But as Jim and I discovered...

14
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,000
No!

15
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Any blow to the pumpkin itself could prove fatal to me.

16
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
At first I drove myself crazy thinking about the things I should have done differently.

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,000
I never should have played that joke on Aaron.

18
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,000
I never should have hollowed out this damn pumpkin in the first place.

19
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
But then I realized I was being silly.

20
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
I mean, the pumpkin should rot off of my head in a month or two.

21
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Right?

22
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Ah!

23
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Ah!

24
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Ah!

25
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Ah!

26
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Yeah!

27
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Ah!

28
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Ha ha ha ha ha!

29
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Woo!

30
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Woo!

31
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Yeah!

32
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Ha ha ha ha ha!

33
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Hey guys.

34
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Hey.

35
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Pam, what are you?

36
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,000
I'm Cinderella.

37
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Cece's really into princesses now, so we decided to turn them into positive female role models.

38
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
I'm an oncologist.

39
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
And you are a dog.

40
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
I'm a puppy.

41
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Dang it.

42
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
I was worried that would happen.

43
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,000
It's okay.

44
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Um, Jim.

45
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,000
You're not dressed up at all.

46
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Sure am.

47
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,000
I am...

48
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,000
One of the men in black eyes.

49
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Can I have your sunglasses?

50
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Jim, come on.

51
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
I thought we were past this.

52
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,000
So, the sports marketing business that Jim told everyone about except for me...

53
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:59,000
There's a big investment lunch today, so I decided to skip the costume.

54
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Unless he has a secret costume that he told everyone about except for me.

55
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Getting a lot of mileage out of this, aren't you?

56
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Yeah, we'll get used to it, bud.

57
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
A cheetah bug.

58
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Ha ha ha ha!

59
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,000
You guys look great!

60
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Just a reminder, the party is right after lunch, so make sure you get all your work done before that or throw it out.

61
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Any questions?

62
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
The senator will be joining us later.

63
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Not a question.

64
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,000
No, it wasn't.

65
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Excellent.

66
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
That reminds me, has anyone seen Treble?

67
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Anyone?

68
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Could have sworn I saw some Treble somewhere.

69
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Oh, ladies and gentlemen, here comes Treble!

70
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I'm a man, a man without conviction.

71
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:47,000
You come and go, you come and go.

72
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Come a, come a, come a, come a chameleon.

73
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:57,000
You come and go, you come and go.

74
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Loving would be easy if your colors were like my dreams.

75
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Red, gold, and green. Red, gold, and green.

76
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
Come a, come on!

77
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Ah! So good!

78
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
What lab did these little clones escape from?

79
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
My Cornell acapella group.

80
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,000
You were in an acapella group?

81
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,000
You went to Cornell?

82
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Yeah, okay, ha ha ha ha.

83
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,000
But you have no idea how lucky you are

84
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
because HCT is doing a set at our Halloween party.

85
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Ugh, I don't want to sit through a whole concert of that.

86
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
I do. I love the boss's interest.

87
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
That a boy, Clark.

88
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Where are your boys staying?

89
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
How does it work in the room?

90
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Should you get a privacy partition?

91
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
No, no, no, no, no, no, stay away.

92
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
They're staying with me. Us, actually.

93
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Aaron's got all the tenors and I got all the basses and B-tones.

94
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Jealous.

95
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
You know what I just realized?

96
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:55,000
They might actually call me up to solo on George Michael's Faith.

97
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
That was one of my signature songs.

98
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Oh man, that would be insane.

99
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
I'm so not prepared.

100
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Hosting the guys in my studio apartment has been no problem.

101
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
They took the bed.
